</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/dezeen/~4/zW74BLyioRo" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:22:"http://www.dezeen.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:6:"Dezeen";}s:32:"64e5af9fad5441475fe8e8acc773dea2";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:73:"Facebook reportedly hires former Apple iOS 6 Maps lead Richard Williamson";s:4:"link";s:94:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/facebook-reportedly-hires-former-apple-ios-6-maps-overseer/";s:6:"author";s:10:"Jon Fingas";s:4:"date";i:1366134960;s:7:"content";s:2661:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/facebook-reportedly-hires-former-apple-ios-6-maps-overseer/"><img alt="Facebook reportedly hires former Apple iOS 6 Maps overseer Richard Williamson" data-src-height="340" data-src-width="620" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/ios6-maps-broken-340.jpg"></a></p><p> Among the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/10/29/apple-executive-shakeup-scott-forstall-and-john-browett-out/">people affected</a> by Apple's iOS 6 <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/09/28/tim-cook-apologizes-for-maps-mess/">Maps debacle</a> was claimed project head <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/11/27/apple-richard-williamson-fired-maps-ios-6/">Richard Williamson</a>, who was reportedly shown the door at the end of 2012. While the details were never directly corroborated outside of Williamson's exit in December, he may have found a new home at Facebook: <em>Bloomberg</em>'s sources say that the director joined the social network's mobile software division within the past two weeks. We don't know what (if anything) Williamson might be producing when Facebook has so far declined comment, although there's no question that he has an appropriate pedigree when he managed interface development for key iOS apps and helped get Safari <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/07/apple-safari-marks-its-10th-birthday-as-part-of-a-much-wider-web/">off the ground</a>. Suffice it to say that the internet giant has <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/09/htc-first-with-facebook-home-review/">plenty</a> of <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/facebook-updating-iphone-app-to-add-chat-head-support-today/">projects</a> that might benefit from his overall experience.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/cellphones/" rel="tag">Cellphones</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/internet/" rel="tag">Internet</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/" rel="tag">Mobile</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/apple/" rel="tag">Apple</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/facebook/" rel="tag">Facebook</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/facebook-reportedly-hires-former-apple-ios-6-maps-overseer/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Via:</strong> <a href="http://appleinsider.com/articles/13/04/16/facebook-reportedly-hires-ex-apple-maps-chief-to-mobile-software-team" target="_blank">AppleInsider</a><!--//--></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a href="http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-16/facebook-said-to-hire-apple-maps-executive-amid-mobile-push.html" target="_blank">Bloomberg</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"7fe50361901dda6b1c579d73e2facc11";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:80:"Prescription Painkiller Dispenser Curbs Abuse By Only Releasing Meds on Schedule";s:4:"link";s:135:"http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~3/3EYN6uTyhyk/prescription-painkiller-dispenser-curbs-abuse-by-only-releasing-meds-on-schedule";s:6:"author";s:16:"Andrew Liszewski";s:4:"date";i:1366134000;s:7:"content";s:4152:"<div> <!-- div style="background-color: #B3B3B3; width: 190px; padding: 1px;"><a title="Click here to read Prescription Painkiller Dispenser Curbs Abuse By Only Releasing Meds on Schedule" href="http://gizmodo.com/medicine/" style="background-color:#888888; color:#FFFFFF; font-size:12px;text-align:right; display:block; height:14px; padding:1px 2px; text-decoration:none; text-transform:uppercase; width:156px;"><span style="color: white;" class="hash">#</span><span style="color: white;">medicine</span></a></div --> <div><a title="Click here to read Prescription Painkiller Dispenser Curbs Abuse By Only Releasing Meds on Schedule" href="http://gizmodo.com/5994789/prescription-painkiller-dispenser-curbs-abuse-by-only-releasing-meds-on-schedule"> <img height="360" width="640" title="Click here to read Prescription Painkiller Dispenser Curbs Abuse By Only Releasing Meds on Schedule" alt="Click here to read Prescription Painkiller Dispenser Curbs Abuse By Only Releasing Meds on Schedule" src="http://img.gawkerassets.com/img/18ktmptlft759jpg/xlarge.jpg"></a></div> </div> The sense of euphoria and release that comes from taking prescription painkillers can often lead to users getting addicted, and possibly even overdose if things get out of hand. So to prevent this from happening, students at Brigham Young University have <a href="http://news.byu.edu/archive13-apr-medvaultcapstone.aspx">developed an advanced pill dispenser</a> that only releases meds on a doctor's or pharmacist's preset schedule. <a href="http://gizmodo.com/5994789/prescription-painkiller-dispenser-curbs-abuse-by-only-releasing-meds-on-schedule" title="Click here to read more about Prescription Painkiller Dispenser Curbs Abuse By Only Releasing Meds on Schedule">More&nbsp;&raquo;</a> <br><img width="1" height="1" src="http://gizmodo.feedsportal.com/c/34976/f/647164/s/2acab693/mf.gif" border="0"><div><table border="0"><tr><td valign="middle"><a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/twitter/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994789%2Fprescription-painkiller-dispenser-curbs-abuse-by-only-releasing-meds-on-schedule&amp;t=Prescription+Painkiller+Dispenser+Curbs+Abuse+By+Only+Releasing+Meds+on+Schedule" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/twitter.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/facebook/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994789%2Fprescription-painkiller-dispenser-curbs-abuse-by-only-releasing-meds-on-schedule&amp;t=Prescription+Painkiller+Dispenser+Curbs+Abuse+By+Only+Releasing+Meds+on+Schedule" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/facebook.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/linkedin/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994789%2Fprescription-painkiller-dispenser-curbs-abuse-by-only-releasing-meds-on-schedule&amp;t=Prescription+Painkiller+Dispenser+Curbs+Abuse+By+Only+Releasing+Meds+on+Schedule" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/linkedin.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/gplus/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994789%2Fprescription-painkiller-dispenser-curbs-abuse-by-only-releasing-meds-on-schedule&amp;t=Prescription+Painkiller+Dispenser+Curbs+Abuse+By+Only+Releasing+Meds+on+Schedule" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/googleplus.png" border="0"></a>&nbsp;<a href="http://share.feedsportal.com/share/email/?u=http%3A%2F%2Fgizmodo.com%2F5994789%2Fprescription-painkiller-dispenser-curbs-abuse-by-only-releasing-meds-on-schedule&amp;t=Prescription+Painkiller+Dispenser+Curbs+Abuse+By+Only+Releasing+Meds+on+Schedule" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png" border="0"></a></td></tr></table></div><br><br><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644742884/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2acab693/a2.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644742884/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2acab693/a2.img" border="0"></a><img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163644742884/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2acab693/a2t.img" border="0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~4/3EYN6uTyhyk" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:19:"http://gizmodo.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:7:"Gizmodo";}s:32:"9ad047236591b29d7d88e2056e2bc515";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:57:"Glass Explorer Edition gets unboxed, photographed (video)";s:4:"link";s:84:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/glass-explorer-edition-gets-unboxed-photographed/";s:6:"author";s:13:"Alexis Santos";s:4:"date";i:1366133580;s:7:"content";s:2586:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/glass-explorer-edition-gets-unboxed-photographed/"><img alt="Glass Explorer Edition gets unboxed, photographed" data-src-height="297" data-src-width="619" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/glass-explorer-edition.jpg"></a></p><p> We already know what Page and Co. will be <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/google-glass-support-page-lists-tech-specs-for-camera-battery/">packing along with</a> Glass, but now that participants of the Explorer program have begun <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/google-glass-explorer-editions-rolling-off-production-line-to-ship-in-waves/">picking up the wearable hardware</a>, we're getting a second-hand unboxing experience. For those in need of a refresher, the glasses will be accompanied by a microUSB cable and charger, a pouch and an attachable shade and clear lens. Though there isn't much to glean from the stream of images, one of Mountain View's adventurers noticed that users will be able to send navigation directions straight from a smartphone to the eyewear. Click the source links below to take a gander at the photos, or hit the jump to watch a video shot with Glass by a Googler.</p><p> <strong>Update 1:</strong> We've slotted in a video after the break of Glass user Dan McLaughlin <span>extracting his device from its packaging. The footage is a bit choppy, but it certainly provides a closer look at the hardware.</span></p><p> <strong>Update 2:</strong> The intrepid folks at <em>Tinhte</em> managed to get their mitts on Google's headgear and have given us a tour -- albeit in Vietnamese -- of the contraption, replete with close-ups and solid video quality. Head past the break to watch the footage.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/wearables/" rel="tag">Wearables</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/google/" rel="tag">Google</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/glass-explorer-edition-gets-unboxed-photographed/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://plus.google.com/u/0/102178182849845958879/posts/LkJHGMMfZG8">Brandon Allgood (Google+)</a><!--//-->, <a target="_blank" href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/114375401846819599162/posts/gHR1cGqDrGp">Cecilia Abadie (Google+)</a><!--//-->, <a target="_blank" href="https://plus.google.com/u/0/114808282876163544785/posts/TwJbRMDjewD">Matt Abdou (Google+)</a><!--//-->, <a target="_blank" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YliQxNIvCts">Dan McLaughlin</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"2c77395c68f3c276c0775643d4e58804";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:90:"New Star Trek Into Darkness Trailer: You'll Never Believe What the Enterprise Has to Fight";s:4:"link";s:149:"http://feeds.gawker.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~3/LLAvqnH5vsI/new-star-trek-into-darkness-trailer-explosions-mass-destruction-and-the-greatest-pep-talk-ever";s:6:"author";s:11:"Kyle Wagner";s:4:"date";i:1366133041;s:7:"content";s:4364:"<div> <!-- div style="background-color: #B3B3B3; width: 190px; padding: 1px;"><a title="Click here to read New Star Trek Into Darkness Trailer: You'll Never Believe What the Enterprise Has to Fight" href="http://gizmodo.com/star-trek/" style="background-color:#888888; color:#FFFFFF; font-size:12px;text-align:right; display:block; height:14px; padding:1px 2px; text-decoration:none; text-transform:uppercase; width:156px;"><span style="color: white;" class="hash">#</span><span style="color: white;">startrek</span></a></div --> <div><a title="Click here to read New Star Trek Into Darkness Trailer: You'll Never Believe What the Enterprise Has to Fight" href="http://gizmodo.com/5994796/new-star-trek-into-darkness-trailer-explosions-mass-destr