vailable-on-the-iphone&amp;t=Facebook+Is+Talking+to+Apple+About+Making+Facebook+Home+for+the+iPhone" target="_blank"><img src="http://res3.feedsportal.com/social/email.png" border="0"></a></td></tr></table></div><br><br><a href="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644627343/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ac190dc/kg/342/a2.htm"><img src="http://da.feedsportal.com/r/163644627343/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ac190dc/kg/342/a2.img" border="0"></a><img width="1" height="1" src="http://pi.feedsportal.com/r/163644627343/u/49/f/647164/c/34976/s/2ac190dc/kg/342/a2t.img" border="0"><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/gizmodo/full/~4/oWS3TvaE_WU" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:19:"http://gizmodo.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:7:"Gizmodo";}s:32:"46d87963d0f239e74bb752cf0effdc57";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:77:"SugarSync for iOS gets an all-new design, multi-platform search functionality";s:4:"link";s:60:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/sugarsync-for-ios-update/";s:6:"author";s:13:"Edgar Alvarez";s:4:"date";i:1366072440;s:7:"content";s:2171:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/sugarsync-for-ios-update/"><img alt="SugarSync for iOS gets an allnew design, multiplatform search functionality" data-src-height="450" data-src-width="527" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/sugarsyncios415.jpg"></a></p><p> It wasn't too long ago that SugarSync <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/02/15/sugarsync-2-0-now-official-with-drag-and-drop-sharing/">overhauled</a> a couple of the apps it serves on different platforms, but for whatever reason the iOS version wasn't included in that round of updates. Today, though, the cloud-based storage service is releasing a new version of its application for Apple devices that brings a fair bit to the table. Chief among the improvements is a completely redesigned UI that, according to the company, aims to provide a more consistent experience across all the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/01/04/sugarsync-brings-autosync-technology-to-videos/">apps it currently offers</a>.</p><p> iPod touch, iPhone <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/03/23/sugarsync-3-0-hits-the-ipad-with-revamped-interface/">and iPad</a> users will also now see a new feature which allows any saved file on SugarSync to be searched from within the app, while "Open In" integrates deeply with the OS to make it easier to open / save docs via other services. <a href="http://www.engadget.com/tag/sugarsync/">SugarSync</a> is also quick to point out that there are many more iOS features in the works (such as labels for folders), but we'll have to wait until a future release for those.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/cellphones/" rel="tag">Cellphones</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/software/" rel="tag">Software</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/" rel="tag">Mobile</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/apple/" rel="tag">Apple</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/sugarsync-for-ios-update/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/sugarsync/id288491637?mt=8">App Store</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"cf6f4fa09fd9c77d5b5dfce79adaae8e";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:41:"Faith Hill Leaves 'Sunday Night Football'";s:4:"link";s:92:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/thr/news/~3/QqbmFz3GFmk/faith-hill-leaves-sunday-night-439824";s:6:"author";s:11:"Philiana Ng";s:4:"date";i:1366072275;s:7:"content";s:1684:"<img src="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/sites/default/files/2013/04/faith_hill_a_p.jpg"><br>The singer will not return when NBC kicks off a new season later this year.<p><a href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/faith-hill-leaves-sunday-night-439824" target="_blank">read more</a></p><div>
