</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/thr/news/~4/O3IfwVUCx4A" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:33:"http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:18:"Hollywood Reporter";}s:32:"b6fe81a6d14100ad1e28ecc5401b56db";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:65:"YouTube for iOS updated to support live streams, TV video queuing";s:4:"link";s:83:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/youtube-for-ios-updated-to-support-live-streams/";s:6:"author";s:10:"Jon Fingas";s:4:"date";i:1366063860;s:7:"content";s:1741:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/youtube-for-ios-updated-to-support-live-streams/"><img alt="YouTube for iOS" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/02/youtube-ios-send-to-tv.jpg"></a></p><p> Google, we have to talk about your sense of timing. You've just streamed <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/12/google-t-mobile-streaming-coachella-2013/">Coachella's first weekend</a> on YouTube, and <em>now</em> you update the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/02/28/youtube-for-ios-adds-send-to-tv-pairing/">YouTube app for iOS</a> to support live video? Better late than never, we suppose. Thankfully, there's a pair of extra features in the bargain, including the ability to queue multiple videos for TV viewing and a port of the Android version's uploads-only My Subscriptions feed. While it'll be awhile before we recover from missing the Tegan and Sara show, everyone can prepare for future events by upgrading at the source link.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/cellphones/" rel="tag">Cellphones</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/tablets/" rel="tag">Tablets</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/" rel="tag">Mobile</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/google/" rel="tag">Google</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/16/youtube-for-ios-updated-to-support-live-streams/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Via:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.theverge.com/2013/4/15/4227482/youtube-update-adds-support-for-live-streaming-on-ios">The Verge</a><!--//--></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="https://itunes.apple.com/app/youtube/id544007664?mt=8">App Store</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"e1ba85a6a67965fefe9d9631c16e30f6";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:52:"Kate Upton Joining Cameron Diaz in 'The Other Woman'";s:4:"link";s:93:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/thr/news/~3/hheElWLnXUs/kate-upton-joining-cameron-diaz-439793";s:6:"author";s:9:"Borys Kit";s:4:"date";i:1366063419;s:7:"content";s:1700:"<img src="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/sites/default/files/2013/04/kate_upton_headshot_a_p_0.jpg"><br>Leslie Mann and Nikolaj Coster-Waldau already are on board the revenge comedy. <p><a href="http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/kate-upton-joining-cameron-diaz-439793" target="_blank">read more</a></p><div>
