</div><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/dezeen/~4/mAhArpmvWlk" height="1" width="1">";s:9:"feed_link";s:22:"http://www.dezeen.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:6:"Dezeen";}s:32:"3fce55548836a524b8bfc5ebb3014130";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:54:"T-Mobile leak hints at an HTC One launch on April 24th";s:4:"link";s:90:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/t-mobile-leak-hints-at-an-htc-one-launch-on-april-24th/";s:6:"author";s:10:"Jon Fingas";s:4:"date";i:1366038240;s:7:"content";s:1989:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/t-mobile-leak-hints-at-an-htc-one-launch-on-april-24th/"><img alt="TMobile leak hints at an HTC One launch on April 24th" data-src-height="390" data-src-width="619" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/htc-one-t-mobile-april-24-leak.jpg"></a></p><p> We've known for a while that April 19th is the big day for <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/08/htc-one-for-att-sprint-review/">AT&amp;T and Sprint versions</a> of the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/03/12/htc-one-review/">HTC One</a>, yet news of the T-Mobile version's release has been thin. If <em>TmoNews</em>' copy of a staff memo is on target, though, the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/tag/UnCarrier/">UnCarrier's</a> subscribers will only have to wait until April 24th to get their turn. The note tells workers that "select stores" will have the One that day -- it doesn't mention which stores those might be, but it's safe to say this could mean a launch later than the one <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/08/best-buy-shipping-htc-one-for-t-mobile-starting-april-19th/">Best Buy claimed</a> days ago. When we already know the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/03/26/t-mobile-iphone-liveblog/#post-38310">$99 regular price</a>, about all that's seemingly left is for T-Mobile to give the final word.</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/cellphones/" rel="tag">Cellphones</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/" rel="tag">Mobile</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/htc/" rel="tag">HTC</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/t-mobile/" rel="tag">T-Mobile</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/t-mobile-leak-hints-at-an-htc-one-launch-on-april-24th/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.tmonews.com/2013/04/second-screenshot-confirms-april-24th-htc-one-launch-date/">TmoNews</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"88d66e1fa1aa5703ef028c6ee7e661e2";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:49:"Got a sec? Clear some Tetris lines on your Pebble";s:4:"link";s:50:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/pebblis-pebble/";s:6:"author";s:11:"Ben Gilbert";s:4:"date";i:1366037400;s:7:"content";s:2721:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/pebblis-pebble/"><img alt="Got a sec Clear some Tetris lines on your Pebble" data-src-height="411" data-src-width="619" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/pebbliswmedhedimg619px.jpg"></a></p><p> Put that silly smartphone back in your pocket, <em>Tetris</em> fan! The Pebble e-paper watch is now able to do more than just tell you when you've received a new SMS and <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/03/20/pebble-firmware-update/">play <em>Snake</em></a> -- a new application called "Pebblis" clones the iconic Russian puzzle game for Pebble with stunning accuracy. Even better? It's free, and super easy to get working. All we had to do with our Android was click through <a href="http://forums.getpebble.com/discussion/4280/tetris-clone">the source link</a> and the Pebble app took care of the rest. Apparently it's a bit tougher to get running via iOS, but then again, Pebblis isn't really an "official" application anyway. And yes, playing <em>Tetris</em> on a watch is pretty difficult. <em>Obviously</em>.</p><div><p><strong>Gallery: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/pebblis-tetris-on-pebble/">Pebblis (Tetris on Pebble)</a></strong></p><a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/pebblis-tetris-on-pebble/5813801"><img src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/pebblis1_thumbnail.jpg" alt="" title=""></a><a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/pebblis-tetris-on-pebble/5813802"><img src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/pebblis2_thumbnail.jpg" alt="" title=""></a><a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/pebblis-tetris-on-pebble/5813803"><img src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/pebblis3_thumbnail.jpg" alt="" title=""></a><a href="http://www.engadget.com/photos/pebblis-tetris-on-pebble/5813804"><img src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/04/pebblis4_thumbnail.jpg" alt="" title=""></a></div><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/gaming/" rel="tag">Gaming</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/peripherals/" rel="tag">Peripherals</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/software/" rel="tag">Software</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/mobile/" rel="tag">Mobile</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/pebblis-pebble/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Via:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=609822135714355&amp;set=a.420451041318133.109642.410852228944681&amp;type=1">Facebook</a><!--//--></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://forums.getpebble.com/discussion/4280/tetris-clone">Pebble Forums</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"0248f3abeef500c9629d838d37d8de7d";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:68:"Dell XPS 18 is up for pre-order online: $900 and up, shipping in May";s:4:"link";s:63:"http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/dell-xps-18-hybrid-preorder/";s:6:"author";s:13:"Sarah Silbert";s:4:"date";i:1366036020;s:7:"content";s:1821:"<p> <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/dell-xps-18-hybrid-preorder/"><img alt="" src="http://www.blogcdn.com/www.engadget.com/media/2013/03/xps18leadimage.jpg"></a></p><p> Add this to the list of Tax Day surprises: the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/03/13/dell-introduces-xps-18-aio/">Dell XPS 18</a> all-in-one is available for pre-order online one day ahead of schedule. The giant tablet / semi-portable desktop won't actually ship until the first week in May, but you can add one of three configurations to your cart now. The entry-level model, with a Pentium processor and a 320GB hard drive, will set you back $900, while Core i3 and Core i5 versions are priced at $1,000 and $1,350, respectively. We liked what we saw when we went hands-on with the 4.85-pound PC: its flip-out feet let you transition between slate and desktop mode easily, and the 1080 capacitive touch display is very crisp. Admittedly, there is only a handful of tabletop Windows 8 slates, but the XPS 18 can hold its own against the <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2012/08/29/sony-vaio-tap-20-hands-on/">Sony VAIO Tap 20</a> and Lenovo's jumbo-sized <a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/01/06/lenovo-horizon-table-pc-hands-on/">Horizon Table PC</a>. Click through to Dell's US site for more details.</p><p> [Thanks, Tom]</p><p>Filed under: <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/desktops/" rel="tag">Desktops</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/tablets/" rel="tag">Tablets</a>, <a href="http://www.engadget.com/category/dell/" rel="tag">Dell</a></p><p><strong><a href="http://www.engadget.com/2013/04/15/dell-xps-18-hybrid-preorder/#comments">Comments</a></strong></p><p><strong>Source:</strong> <a target="_blank" href="http://www.dell.com/us/eep/p/exclusive-pc-deals?link_number=124903199">Dell</a><!--//--></p>";s:9:"feed_link";s:24:"http://www.engadget.com/";s:10:"feed_title";s:17:"Engadget RSS Feed";}s:32:"f0c12d10d28596a4feb7fa82430b8499";a:7:{s:5:"title";s:36:"Vote for Dezeen to win a Webby Award";s:4:"link";s:53:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/dezeen/~3/1TMGL2Qx760/";s:6:"author";s:16:"Rose Etherington";s:4:"date";i:1366035195;s:7:"content";s:1863:"<p><a href="http://pv.webbyawards.com/nominees/online-film-video/general-film-categories/technology" target="_blank"><img src="http://static.dezeen.com/uploads/2013/04/dezeen_Nominated-for-Webby-Award.jpg" alt="Dezeen Philips Lumiblade movie nominated for Webby Award" title="Dezeen Philips Lumiblade movie nominated for Webby Award" width="468" height="468"></a></p>
<p>Our movie about Philips' Lumiblade OLED lighting is <a href="http://pv.webbyawards.com/nominees/online-film-video/general-film-categories/technology" target="_blank">shortlisted in the Technology category</a> of the Webby Awards! <a href="http://pv.webbyawards.com/nominees/online-film-video/general-film-categories/technology" target="_blank">Vote for us to win the People's Voice award</a>.  <a href="http://www.dezeen.com/2013/04/15/vote-for-us-in-the-webby-awards/">(more...)</a></p>
